# Coverage exclusions. Two shapes allowed:
#
#   1. Entry-point shims: cmd/<binary>/main.go is excluded wholesale.
#      Keep main() to bare flag parsing, signal handling, and dependency
#      assembly. Anything testable belongs in internal/* with 100% cov.
#
#   2. Per-package "must" helpers — files named `*_must.go` contain
#      only panic helpers for error branches the production caller
#      cannot trigger (kernel-level pipe allocation, fresh-tempdir
#      failure, post-success Close, etc.). Each helper carries a doc
#      comment justifying why it cannot be reached from a test, and
#      panics rather than returning the impossible error so callers
#      have no leftover `if err != nil` branch to cover.
#
# Reference: slack-acp's AGENTS.md "Coverage" section.
^github.com/kfet/poe-acp/cmd/[^/]+/main\.go:
_must\.go:
